longBusinessSummary: Engine Media Holdings, Inc., together with its subsidiaries, engages in the development and sale of gaming applications. It provides e-sport or sporting event or tournament services; offers content management system, video software, mobile applications, and e-sports data platform solutions; sources, creates, and places advertising campaigns that run-in company's network of publisher sites; and provides installation and website design services, as well as data analysis report delivery. The company also offers Esports platform for online tournaments; content publishing, engagement, and monetization; data analytics and intellectual property solutions; UMG Online, an esports website for daily tournaments and ladders; and racing titles. The company was formerly known as Torque Esports Corp. and changed its name to Engine Media Holdings, Inc. in August 2020. The company was incorporated in 2011 and is headquartered in Toronto, Canada.
